Description:
    Enhances your RubyLLM chat UI with React islands for smooth streaming animations.
    Zero changes to your models - works with existing Turbo Streams.

Example:
    rails generate islandjs_rails:chat_ui

Creates:
    React Components (3):
        app/javascript/islands/components/ChatMessage.jsx
        app/javascript/islands/components/StreamingContent.jsx
        app/javascript/islands/components/ChatContainer.jsx
    
    Views (2):
        app/views/messages/_message_island.html.erb
        app/views/island_chats/show.html.erb
    
    Styles (1):
        app/assets/stylesheets/chat_islands.css

Modifies:
    app/controllers/islandjs_demo_controller.rb  (adds react_chat action)
    config/routes.rb                              (adds demo route)
    app/views/chats/show.html.erb                 (adds comparison link)

Prerequisites:
    • RubyLLM installed: gem 'ruby_llm'
    • Run: rails generate ruby_llm:chat_ui
    • Layout must have: <%= islands %> in <head>

Usage:
    1. Generate the chat UI:
       $ rails generate islandjs_rails:chat_ui
    
    2. Start development servers:
       $ yarn watch          # Terminal 1
       $ bin/rails server    # Terminal 2
    
    3. Compare the UIs:
       /chats/:id                    → Standard UI
       /islandjs/react/chats/:id     → Island UI (with animations)
    
    4. Use in your own views:
       <%= render 'messages/message_island', message: @message %>

Features:
    ✨ Character-by-character streaming
    ✨ Blinking cursor animation
    ✨ Progressive enhancement (works without JS)
    ✨ Side-by-side comparison demo
    ✨ Zero model modifications required
